## Operating Rules

- Keep durable project guidance in `AGENTS.md`.
- Keep reusable agent roles in `.codex/agents/` only when they are safe to
  share with the repository.
- Keep private overlays, local manifests, tokens, and workstation paths out of
  version control.
- Run dry-run install commands before writing global or project agent files.
- Keep validation commands narrow to the files changed.

## Suggested Agent Roles

Install global roles from the source dev-skills checkout. Set `DEV_SKILLS` to
that checkout path first:

```bash
export DEV_SKILLS="$dev_skills_path"
python3 "$DEV_SKILLS/subagents/hardened-codex/scripts/sync_agents.py" --global --dry-run
```

Install a project overlay into this checkout only after reviewing the planned
copy actions:

```bash
python3 "$DEV_SKILLS/subagents/hardened-codex/scripts/sync_agents.py" \
  --overlay tooling \
  --project-dir "$PWD" \
  --dry-run
```

## Rollback

The hardened installer creates timestamped backups below `.codex/agent-backups`
for project installs and `~/.codex/agent-backups` for global installs. Restore
from the newest backup directory if an agent role needs to be reverted.

## Minimum Smoke

```bash
git status --short
git diff --check
```

